{% block content %}
	<!-- Intro -->
	<div id="intro">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="panel panel-primary col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
				<div class="col-md-5">
					<img src="/public/images/mwux-2016.png" alt="mwux cincinnati 2016" class="img-responsive" />
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-7 p2">
					<p>UX is changing at lightning speed, and Cincinnati is, too. Since 2004, more than $834 million has been invested in redevelopment and new construction in Cincinnati’s urban core. There’s a major transformation happening in the city, and we’d love to share this new Cincinnati experience with Midwest UX attendees. We envision a conference that covers what’s now, what’s next and how to bridge the gap between the two. Think of Midwest UX Cincinnati as the perfect match between a city and an industry both going places.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<!-- Process -->
	<div id="process">
		<div class="container p4">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
					<h1 class="text-uppercase text-center">The Application Process</h1>
					<p>In 2015, the entire UX design team from Gaslight, a software design and development firm in Cincinnati, headed for Midwest UX. They came back from the event inspired, informed and downright fired up. We immediately started talking about how cool it would be to bring the conference to Cincinnati. Eventually, we told some local friends about our dream, and soon enough, we’d all pitched in to create this application. Our biggest goal? Make other folks feel as excited as we did after Midwest UX Indianapolis.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<!-- Timeline -->
	<div id="timeline">
		<div class="container">
			<h1 class="text-uppercase text-center mt3 mb3">Event Planning Timeline</h1>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">12 Months <small>Before</small></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<p class="lead">Event chairs determine and appoint key Committee Chairs. Appointing specific committee chairs helps distribute the work. However, event chairs guide the overall purpose and vision of the event and cannot avoid working closely with each chair. Expected committee chairs:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Corporate Relations/Sponsorships Chair (immediately)</li>
						<li>Design Chair (immediately)</li>
						<li>Volunteer Coordinator Chair (no later than 9 months before event) </li>
						<li>Marketing & Public Relations Chair (immediately) </li>
						<li>Speaker Curator Chair</li>
						<li>Speaker Relations Chair</li>
						<li>Establish a theme/vision for the event </li>
						<li>Establish a more detailed budget, including expenses and revenue:
							<ul>
								<li>Venue & service</li>
								<li>Catering</li>
								<li>Labor</li>
								<li>Publishing costs</li>
								<li>Special equipment</li>
								<li>Entertainment</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
						<li>Establish location, time & date for Midwest UX Cincinnati</li>
						<li>Book venue: make deposits and sign contracts if necessary </li>
						<li>Create a more detailed event timeline</li>
						<li>Set absolute deadlines and plan accordingly to achieve them. </li>
						<li>Gather assets from Midwest UX 2015: email lists, past attendees, past speakers, sponsor records, budgets, attendee feedback, etc. </li>
						<li>Set up call with Midwest UX 2015 chairs: gather advice, insights, etc. </li>
						<li>Send press release to local media that Cincinnati was chosen as Midwest UX host to start creating excitement and recruiting volunteers. </li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">9 Months <small>Before</small></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<ul>
						<li>Appoint last Committee Chairs </li>
						<li>Committee chairs recruit committee members</li>
						<li>Initial committee meetings begin</li>
						<li>Individual committees begin to plan the details of each area and adhere to budget constraints determined by event chairs </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Speaker Curator</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Create call for speakers</li>
						<li>Outline speakers slots and tracks, creating a mix of topics and session types</li>
						<li>Outline a process for choosing speaker slate</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Logistics Committee</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Determine flow and timing of event</li>
						<li>Determine volunteers needed</li>
						<li>Brainstorm ideas for new and unique experiences</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Decorations Committee</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Begin to determine theme</li>
						<li>Start cost evaluations</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Corporate Relations/Sponsorships Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Begin sponsorship solicitations</li>
						<li>Mail packets and meet potential sponsors in person</li>
						<li>Get high powered, influential people involved in the ask</li>
						<li>Follow-up bi-weekly until you get an answer</li>
						<li>If corporations are not interested in sponsoring the event at-large, ask them to commit to purchase several tickets</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Marketing and PR Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Create an overall marketing and communications strategy</li>
						<li>Outline a tactical calendar for carrying out that strategy</li>
						<li>Meet with other conference chairs to talk about marketing support needs</li>
						<li>Work with design chair to launch initial event website</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Design Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Create an overall look and feel for the event</li>
						<li>Design and launch initial website (work with marketing/PR chair on content)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">7 – 6 Months <small>Before</small></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<h4>Event Chair(s)</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Begin monthly meetings for all Committee Chairs <small>(Keep this a standing date to ensure attendance.)</small></li>
						<li>Each committee reports progress and expresses needs</li>
						<li>Reconcile budget</li>
						<li>Go over budget with the Committee Chairs keeping close tabs on what each Committee spends</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Speaker Curator</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Release call for speakers</li>
						<li>Work with marketing chair to promote call for speakers</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Corporate Relations/Sponsorships Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Continue with sponsorship solicitations and table/ticket sales</li>
						<li>Start to collect sponsor logos for use in PR and signage</li>
						<li>Ask sponsors to participate in volunteering for event</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Media & Public Relations Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Promote call for speakers: email campaign, social media campaign, reach out to key contacts for co-promotion, etc. </li>
						<li>Continue to hold monthly committee meetings </li>
						<li>Begin to publish promotional content for event <small>(blog posts, articles, etc.)</small></li>
						<li>Promote early ticket sales: email campaign, social media campaign, reach out to key influencers/bloggers, etc.</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Event Chair(s)</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Start early ticket sales </li>
						<li>Go over budget with the Committee Chairs keeping close tabs on what each Committee spends </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Corporate Relations/Sponsorships Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Mail second invoices to corporate sponsors (if necessary) </li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">4 Months <small>Before</small></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<h4>Event Chair(s)</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Visit event venue</li>
						<li>Continue holding monthly committee meetings</li>
						<li>Go over budget with the Committee Chairs keeping close tabs on what each Committee spends</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Speaker Curator</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Choose final speaker line-up</li>
						<li>Notify speakers</li>
						<li>Pass talk titles, descriptions, speaker names, headshots, etc., to marketing</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Corporate Relations/Sponsorship Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Report your progress to sponsors</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Event Chair(s)</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Start bi-weekly Committee meetings</li>
						<li>Go over budget with the Committee Chairs keeping close tabs on what each Committee spends</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Marketing & Public Relations Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Release conference speakers and talks on website</li>
						<li>Run email and social campaign around speakers to drive ticket sales</li>
						<li>Provide speakers with promotional tweets, FB posts, etc., to share</li>
						<li>Send press release with speaker line-up</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Design Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Start working on any signage/design needs for event: badges, posters, wayfinding, etc.</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Catering Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Begin to focus on menu options</li>
						<li>Work closely with caterer</li>
						<li>Don't forget to consider special dietary needs of guests</li>
						<li>Set up time for tasting of the menu if necessary</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">2 Months <small>Before</small></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<h4>Logistics Committee Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Get volunteers committed for the day of the event</li>
						<li>Clarify any parking issues that might be attached to using the venue</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Entertainment/Program Committee Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Final considerations</li>
						<li>Sound systems</li>
						<li>Transporting heavy objects</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Event Chair(s)</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Continue with bi-weekly committee meetings</li>
						<li>Go over budget with the Committee Chairs keeping close tabs on what each Committee spends</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Volunteer coordinator</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Should meet with each committee chair to determine needs</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Corporate Relations/ Sponsorship Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Start to design signs for sponsors in coordination with Design Chair</li>
						<li>Be sure to use the most updated logo</li>
						<li>Report progress to sponsors</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Catering Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Confirm menus with the caterer</li>
						<li>Be sure all rentals have been requested</li>
						<li>Make sure all beverages are set including non-alcoholic beverages</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Marketing & PR Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Continue push for ticket sales</li>
						<li>Continue to execute on tactical marketing plan</li>
						<li>Reach out to regional companies with large UX teams for group ticket sales</li>
					</ul>

				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">1 Month <small>Before</small></h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<h4>Volunteer Coordinator</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Confirm volunteers - tell them where to be and when </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Catering Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Confirm catering </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Entertainment/Program Committee Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Confirm entertainment </li>
						<li>Confirm arrival times: Emcee, entertainment, and volunteers </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Event Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Print out guest list in alphabetical order for the check-in volunteers </li>
						<li>Generate checks for entertainment and caterer if required </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Marketing & Public Relations Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Final ticket sale push (if any are left)</li>
						<li>Offer comped tickets to a few key media people</li>
						<li>Coordinate any media interviews with speakers/key organizers</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Design Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Coordinate final signage production </li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">Day of Event</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<h4>Entertainment/Program Committee Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Be sure all necessary sound equipment is delivered early on the day of the event in case of problems Day of the event </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>All Event & Committee Chairs </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Arrive for set up </li>
						<li>Work in shifts </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Volunteer Coordinator </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Lead his/her troops </li>
						<li>Keep timeline close at hand all evening to check the status </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Catering Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Walk through event one final time with the caterer </li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Entertainment/Program Committee Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Have featured entertainment and speakers in place 20 minutes before you need them</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Design Chair</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Deliver all signage and design elements to event</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>


			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<h2 class="text-center">Post Event Follow-up </h2>
				</div>
				<div class="panel col-md-9">
					<h4>Event Chair </h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Reconcile budget </li>
						<li>Collect any outstanding money or pledges </li>
						<li>Mail or deliver all expenses from event </li>
						<li>Send thank you notes to all committee members </li>
						<li>Send a report to all sponsors with a thank you </li>
						<li>Send evaluation request and thank you to all attendees</li>
					</ul>

					<h4>Follow-up</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Send follow-up communications to all special guests encouraging them to continue to support the organization</li>
						<li>Collect all articles and press clippings </li>
						<li>Meet with individual committees 2 to 5 days after the event for evaluation </li>
						<li>Discuss all successes and challenges of event </li>
						<li>Offer suggestions to remedy problems </li>
						<li>Offer explanations as to why certain things did and did not work </li>
						<li>Save all notes and compile a notebook for reference to future chairs </li>
						<li>Include all budget to actual information </li>
						<li>Include receipts </li>
						<li>Include planning notes from each committee chair </li>
						<li>Include all press releases </li>
						<li>Include sample letters sent to sponsors </li>
						<li>Include attendee lists </li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>
	</div>

