	<!-- Cincinnati -->
	<div id="cincinnati">
		<div class="container mt8">
			<div class="row">
				<h1 class="text-center text-uppercase mb2">Design in Cincinnati</h1>
				<div class="col-md-5">
					<p class="lead">There’s a huge design scene in Cincinnati. Ten different Fortune 500 companies are headquartered here, and a thriving community of traditional and digital design agencies support them. Most notably, we’re home to Procter & Gamble, the consumer products giant behind brands like Tide, Pampers and Bounty, and the world’s largest advertiser by annual spend. </p>

					<p>On the tech side, <a href="http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/227439">Entrepreneur magazine called us an “unexpected hub for tech startups.”</a> The Cincinnati-based Brandery earned a spot on Tech Cocktail’s list of <a href="http://tech.co/top-startup-accelerators-ranked-2012-08">Top 15 startup accelerators</a> in the country. More than half of the Brandery’s graduates keep their companies in Cincinnati, and these start-ups are fueling growth in the local UX talent pool. The Cincinnati User Enjoyment UX Meetup, for example, has more than 300 members. </p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-7">
					<h4>Creative Landmarks</h4>
					<p>Just a few highlights of Cincinnati’s creative and design scene:</p>

					<h5><a href="http://daap.uc.edu">DAAP: The University of Cincinnati College of Design, Art, Architecture and Planning</a></h5>
					<p>This local design school is world famous and consistently finds itself at the top of many best of  lists. It makes regular appearances on Business Week’s list of top 30 design schools on the planet. And has received similar recognition from I.D. (International Design) magazine, U.S. News & World report and GDUSA magazine.</p>


					<h5><a href="http://www.howdesign.com/">HOW and PRINT magazines, conferences and design contests</a></h5>
